    <stitle>INTERNATIONAL RIDE OPTIMIZED SUSPENSION (IROS) - MAIN SUPPORT MEMBER</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="repair" graphiccount="1">
        <title>MAIN SUPPORT MEMBER</title>
        <para>The main support member acts as a lightweight one-piece beam to transfer the load directly to the axle and
            also absorb road shock, starting and braking loads.
        </para>
        <figure id="f0301313" figsize="pg-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg03/G0301313.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="312px"
                     scalefitheight="312px"/>
            <caption>Figure 13. Main Support Member</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>1. AIR SPRING LOWER MOUNTING LOCATION</callout1>
                <callout1>2. TAPERED LEAF SPRING</callout1>
                <callout1>3. AXLE MOUNTING PLATE LOCATOR PIN</callout1>
                <callout1>4. TAPERED LEAF SPRING BUSHING ASSEMBLY</callout1>
                <callout1>5. TAPER LEAF SPRING BUSHING WRAP</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <para>Remove and install procedures - follow procedures outlined under MAIN SUPPORT MEMBER in the COMPONENT
            REMOVAL and COMPONENT INSTALLATION sections.
        </para>
    </svcproc>
